Comments: "August: Out in the Black Hills, South Dakota near Hisega. From left to right; Murray, Nancy, Charley, Aunt Helen, John, Barbara, Janice. The horses bumped so hard it almost made the girls cry."

"June: All the Scouts around the campfire at Scout Camp, Dolliver Park. Dining room tent in the background. We have been holding camp here for 15 to 18 years." For more information on the McMurray Boy Scout Troop see this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcy04V4MGIo.
"A Summer in the Sierras: Bill and Doug. Some big yellow pine logs."
"A Summer in the Sierras: Hauling logs by Ox Team"
"A Washout, just by camp. Creek raised 6' in 30 minutes"
"Across a corner of the Yale Campus"
"April: Lt. (j.g.) John McMurry, with his Asiatic and Philippine ribbons, the day he returned home to his very happy family. Tommy and Ann are evidently pleased, too. Taken out back of our house."
"April: Trip to Washington D.C. with Jessie. The White House"
"April: Trip to Washington D.C. with Jessie. Treasury Building"
"April: Trip to Washington D.C. with Jessie. View from the Monument"
"April: Trip to Washington D.C. with Jessie. Washington Monument"

Address: Yale University; Dining Hall, Woolsey Hall, Woodbridge Hall
Comments: "At Dinner Time: Dining Hall "Commons", Woolsey Hall, Woodbridge Hall"
"At the International Aviation Meet Oct, Belmont Park - Long Island: A Wright Biplane"
"At the International Aviation Meet Oct, Belmont Park - Long Island: Dwight and Richard."
"At the International Aviation Meet Oct, Belmont Park - Long Island: Part of the crowd."
"At the International Aviation Meet Oct, Belmont Park - Long Island: The Stand and The Field"

"August 9: This shows the big square of Long Peak looking across 20 miles away from the top of Hallett's Peak. It was climbed by Will Lyman, Milton Frank, Andrew and George McIntosh, Charley, John, and Murray McMurray. Elevation 14,225 feet. Climb plenty hard. Experience one of the high spots of our lives. Went up the cable route, came down the Keyhole."
"August: A big glacier like snow drift on top of the Continental Divide in Colorado. We made snowballs to celebrate."
"August: Anne and Charley on their return from their wedding trip."
"August: Anne at the foot of the Statue of Liberty, the time we went out to see it and all climbed up to the very top."
"August: Anne's 21st birthday on the 2nd story porch at Ocean Grove. First celebration we ever had on the upper porch."
"August: Back door of our cottage at Clear Lake. Hugh and Helen and Nancy just helping load the truck. John's dog, Jack, watching while Howard puts the stuff in the truck."
"August: Charley and Anne at Barnegate Bay Looks like Tarzan and his Mate."
"August: Charley and Anne on the 9th hole at Clear Lake."
"August: Charley, Mother, Jean, Nancy at the Clear Lake golf course. Nancy has just smacked one down the fairway from the first tee."

"August: Elizabeth Lyman getting a drink from Milt on the Fern Lake Trail, while Margaret looks on. One of the man places we stopped for a drink from the clear glacier streams on this hot and dusty trail."
"August: Fern Lake Lodge on Fern Lake in Rocky Mountain National Park. Our group just ready to resume their trip, after spending the night there."
"August: Grandfather and Ann who have just been cleaning fish while the family was at Clear Lake for a few weeks."

"August: John and Jean with Ann and Tommy. This picture was taken at the Plantation on a picnic while Aunt Helen and Uncle Hugh were here. Ann is two years and two months old, Tommy about 3 months old."
"August: John in his Home Guard uniform. This was taken back of our house just before the War Day parade down through the main part of town."

"August: Margaret and Murray loafing on the front porch of 72 Heck Ave. This shows how close the houses are together and the sidewalks just a foot away. We did lots of reading and card playing and loafing on this porch."
"August: Mary in the boat. John and Tommy on the dock. Jack in the water, at Clear Lake."
"August: On the end of our dock at Clear Lake after we have all been swimming."
"August: On the fish wharf in the East River with New York's fishing boats in the foreground and the tall buildings of the city in the background."
"August: On the road to Flat Top Mountain, Hallett Peak. Everybody rode horseback and we finally climbed the last 400 feet. In Rocky Mountain National Park not far from Denver."
"August: On the south Shore of Lake Superior, Ontonagon, Michigan. The McIntosh family and ours were on this trip and we went all through Detroit, northern Michigan and the copper country."
Category Terms: Portraits-Group; Lakes, Rivers, and Streams; Outdoor Recreation

Comments: "August: Our camp in the birches at Fish Creek Pond in the Adirondacks; Janice, Jerry, and the MacIntoshes were with us."
"August: Sunrise on Fern Lake, Rocky Mountain National Park. What we saw when we came from our cabins about six o'clock in the morning to fish for trout a while before we had breakfast."
"August: The bridge across St. Vrain River, going back into the mountains from Wild Basin Campgrounds, Rocky Mountain National Park, Colorado."
Category Terms: Portraits-Group; Lakes, Rivers, and Streams; Outdoor Recreation

Comments: "August: The camp at Galena, Illinois on our way home from our 1939 trip to the Atlantic Coast. About the nicest camp we have ever been in and one which we have often stayed."

"August: This is our camp in Acadia National Forest at Mount Desert Island, Maine. We are beside the road, two tents across and this picture shows the cook tent and two of the sleeping tents. A lovely campground and a wonderful lot of country."

"August: This is the sand beach at Acadia National Park, Mount Desert Island. There was a 12 foot tide here and on the rocks to the right we found a wonderful variety of marine life at low tide. The water was cold as ice and we could only stay in a few minutes."

"August: This is the summer we camped in the Rocky Mountain National Park in Colorado. Here is the view from 100 yards up the hill behind our tent. The two mountains with the snow between them are Hallett's Peak and Flat Top, both of which we climbed."
"August: Tourist Camp, Columbus, Nebraska. John, Jean, our Buick, and the new trailer, on our way to Colorado for the Summer camp."

"August: View from Otter Point looking back from Sand Beach in Acadia National Park near Bar Harbor, Maine. Huguenot Head and Champlain Mountain both of which we climbed, show in the middle background."
"Camp in Redwood Canyon: Bill, Howard, Mc, Dan, Al."
"December: Hayward in our room at Yale"

Comments: "Down "Grub Street", Haughton Hall - Dining Hall at the right"
"Father and Aunt Annie in front of her home"
"In my room at Yale. Old "699 Taylor Hall"."

"January: Ann with her first skates. Taken out on the tennis court, which we iced over. Later this picture was sent to Daddy to show him how nice and cool it was up here while he was so warm down in the South Pacific. Jean knows her picture is going to her husband, while Tommy just hasn't got any skates and says he doesn't like it."

"January: Louisiana State Capitol Building, at Baton Rouge with one of the splendid Live Oaks in the foreground with typical hanging moss. Mother and Dad were visiting Charley over the weekend. In this building Huey Long was shot and from the top of it the splendid view of the Mississippi River and the surrounding country."
"January: The French Quarter in New Orleans where Mother and I went for 4 or 5 days, after spending a very pleasant weekend with Charley, who was in A.S.T.P at Louisiana State at Baton Rouge."
"July: Carl and John with our old Ford truck in the campground at the head of Lake Itasca, Minnesota. This was the first one of many pleasant trips we have taken and our first camping experience."
"July: Father and I at Ocean Grove"
"July: Margaret and I in Millers backyard having our pictures "took"
"July: Ocean Grove at the lower (ocean) end of Wesley Lake"

Comments: "July: One of the groups of Scouts who have enjoyed the week at Clear Lake. From row from left to right: Bob Naden, John Boeye, Charley, Dick Groves, Jim Maxson. Back row: Bill Groves, Rish. Maxson, Murray." For more information on the McMurray Boy Scout Troop see this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcy04V4MGIo.
"July: Some of the Muscovy Ducks raised on the little duck pond at the Plantation that summer."
"July: The familiar old 9th hole at Clear Lake Golf Course with 3 or 4 scouts finishing out the match. This is the course where we have had so many good times and played so many interesting games."
"July: Where Pickett's Charge at Gettysburg was stopped. Lee and George McIntosh and Mother standing by one of the guns."
"June: A Volleyball Game at Scout Camp." For more information on the McMurray Boy Scout Troop see this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcy04V4MGIo.
"June: Hatchery picnic at Briggs Woods one Friday afternoon. About 30 folks went canoeing and wading."
"June: John and Jean, Ann and Tommy at Clear Lake just before John left for the Navy, when we went up to open the cottage for the season."
"June: Prize Tent at Scout Camp. Left to right: Don. Farnham, Bob Ades, Jim Fasset, Charles McMurray, Tent Leader."

"June: Scout Camp in Dolliver Park, just after the tents were all ready for inspection. From 40 to 50 boys have camped here every year for 15 or 18 years." For more information on the McMurray Boy Scout Troop see this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcy04V4MGIo.

"June: Scouts at Scout Camp Dolliver Park, making a human dam across the little creek. Succeeded in actually stopping the water from going over." For more information on the McMurray Boy Scout Troop see this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcy04V4MGIo.
Category Terms: Outdoor Recreation; Lakes, Rivers, and Streams; Children

Comments: "June: Some of the hatchery men about the last day of the season, with a load of chicks ready to go down to the Post Office. Guess they must all be smiling to think of the Clear Lake trip which we were going to take in a few days."

"June: State High School Track Meet held in the athletic stadium Iowa State College, Ames. Charley competed in the Broad Jump, after getting 2nd in the District Meet at Ft. Dodge. Placed 6th, just outside of the money, in the State Meet with a jump of about 20 feet 3 inches."

"June: Tent Leaders at Boy Scout Camp, Dolliver Park. Back row, left to right: Chambers, Welch, Brenneman, Groves, Thompson, Smart, Newman, Brin. Front Row: McMurray, Kneedy, Lewis, Stafford, miith, Nichols, McCollough." For more information on the McMurray Boy Scout Troop see this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcy04V4MGIo.
"June: The Hatchery force in front of the hatchery. 40 strong, 19 men, 21 women. This was the first year we ever sold a million chicks."
"June: The McMurray Chicken Hatchery force, one and all, young and old, down on the plantation for a picnic. 40 people, including Ann McMurray on the front row."
"June: The officials at Scout Camp. Back row, John, Bob Kneedy, Guy Mills, Charley. Front Row: Carl, Murray."
"Looking down Redwood Canyon, "Little Baldy" in the distance"

"March: A Scout Kite Flying Contest held on the Plantation. An annual event that generally several hundred people come to see. The evergreens are getting a good start and Charley's old discus throw marker is plainly visible as are also the mowed paths around the edge of the Plantation." For more information on the McMurray Boy Scout Troop see this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcy04V4MGIo.

"March: John, Charley, and I started down the river in a canoe one afternoon. Right down by Briggs Woods, John saw a big cake of ice floating and climbed out on it. Here he is floating along right opposite where the Scout Fire Building Contests were held."

"March: Webster City Basketball Team. Backrow, left to right: Bob Rozelle (Mgr.), Jim Phillips (guard), Charles McMurray (guard), Wendell Woodall (forward, was on 1st all state), John Wilson (forward), Dick Newman (center), Bob Lamson (coach). Front Row: Bill Castner, Carol Packard, Gayle Maudlin, Vernon Miller, John Hovland, Leon Brin, Bill Chauncy."
"March: Webster City High School First Team. Runners Up State Championship. Phillips, McMurray, guards. Woodall, Wilson, forwards. Newman, center. Lamson, coach."
"May 6: Ann's 5th Birthday. She and Tommy are standing out in front of their tent waving their flags for a message to their daddy, who was way over in the South Pacific on an A.K.A. 71, "The Todd.""

"May: Jerry Fardal taking a picture of John practicing hurtling down on the old Athletic field by the river. This was the year John was a senior in high school, made good time in the hurdles all spring.Got 5th in the low hurdles at the State High School Meet at Ames and qualified in the high hurdles."

"May: The very first Scout Camp in Webster City. Held at Briggs Woods. About 50 boys were there over Memorial and two or three other days." For more information on the McMurray Boy Scout Troop see this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcy04V4MGIo.

"May: Webster City High School Track Team, taken at the Conference Meet at Clarion. Back row, left to right, Lowell, Shot, Discuss, and Javelin; McEwen, Hurdles, Javelin, and Relays; Page, 220 and Relays; Gangsted, Half Mile; Ehlert, Mile; Coach Cassidy, Coach Lamson; McMurray, High Jump, Broad Jump, Shot Put, and Relays. Front row, Hanson, 100 Yard, Half Mile, and Relays; Brenneman, Quarter Mile and Relays; Smart, Broad Jump and Relays."
"May: Webster City Track Team at Britt. These boys took part in the 5 meets. Best track year Webster City has had for quite a while."
"Methodist Church, Lansingburg: Where mother went to church as a girl"
"Nayatt Point across the bay, Narraganset Bay"

Category Terms: Portraits-Individual; Lakes, Rivers, and Streams; Animals

Comments: "Nov: Connecticut Hall where Nathan Hale Roomed"

"November: Webster City High School Football Team, Conference Winners. The backfield just before the last game with Iowa Falls, which Webster City won, left to right: McMurray, McCollough, Crouse, Woodall, Black, Phillips, Ritchie, Packard. Webster City beat Ft. Dodge in a postseason game 14-7."

"October: Andy and Marian and Roger McIntosh, Will and Edna Lymn, John and Mary Gannaway and Margaret in front of Gannaways house at the Grinnell Homecoming. We enjoyed the get-together there and were just leaving for home."
"October: Carl and the 25 lb. White Lake Trout he caught up in Canada. The biggest fish we ever saw caught with a rod and reel and Carl sure worked hard to get it."
"October: Grandpa and the Baby. Murray with his first grandchild, Ann Elizabeth McMurray. She grins at her mother while Grandpa grins at the baby."

"October: John and Jean outside their Circle Villa house at Hollywood, Florida, all dressed in "dress whites". John was an ensign attending Radar school. Jean spent three months with him and this is where Mother and Dad visited and had such a good time."

"October: Mother and Dad getting on the Northwest Air Lines big 42 passenger plane at the Spokane airport. Our first air trip. Had been spending the weekend with Barbara, who was teaching at Colville, Washington and enjoyed very much the lovely country out there."
"October: Scout overnight hike and Coon Hunt at Dolliver Park. Carl on the point, Jim Groves nearest to the camera. This is the night the dogs ran two coons up in the big tree."
"One of the roads. The whole country was flooded."
"Reunion classes on their way to the game"
Category Terms: Entertainment; Main Streets; Schools and Education

Comments: "Sept: Mother and Jessie in the "Garden of the Gods"
"September: "Now boys," Myrtle says, "you do it just like this," while Milt, Earl, and Carl look on enviously. Taken at Inguadona while on a fishing trip."
"September: Although the weather looks warm, it was pretty cold as you can see by the winter dress of the boatsmen. Just coming in from a morning trolling, Earl, Myrtle, and Carl."
"September: Charley and John all ready for a dive off from the bridge between the North and South lake at Inguadona."
"September: Fishing Trip at Inguadonna. Carl, John, Milt, Earl, and Murray. Fishing was the best we have ever seen it. John caught a big 10 lb. Muskelunge this year, not shown in this picture."

"September: Jean and John at the World's Fair in Chicago. This is the first picture we took of them together and we were sort of hoping then it wouldn't be the last. This was the trip that Grandmother McMurray, Margaret, and John and I drove in and met Jean in Chicago."
"September: Lake Inguadona in Minnesota. The old dock along the shore of the lake right near the cottage where we have been fishing so many times."

"September: Milt, Murray, Carl, and John in front of Mr. Spooner's well loved cabin. This must have been taken the first day while it was still warm, as every other day we put lots of clothes on when we came outdoors rather than take them off."
"September: The cabin at Inguadona with Carl, Charley, Mother, and Milt standing in front. Earl and I were also in the party. Where we have caught so many good fish and had so many pleasant times."
Category Terms: Portraits-Group; Landscapes; Lakes, Rivers, and Streams

Comments: "September: The Fishermen's Return or in other words here's the crowd that caught all the fish at Inguadona, with the exception of Jean who had taken Ann to school. Lida and Myrtle proved themselves wonderful fisherwomen and brave sailors on icy cold waters. John caught the biggest fish and Carl, Mother, John, and Myrtle won the Nature Contest."
"Thanksgiving Day: Ocean Grove Beach from the Pier"
